# Cadence retro (2026-05-27) — moving dogfood completeness from memory to a mechanical gate

Cohort: etude-nm6 (gate-record backfill), etude-8hq.4 (build dogfood-completeness
audit), etude-8hq.1 (wire the audit into the close/push path as a hard gate).
8hq.4 + 8hq.1 are the first two beads of phase etude-8hq.

## Trigger
3-ticket cadence, flagged MECHANICALLY this time by the new
`dogfood-completeness-audit.sh` cadence-overdue WARN — not by a human spot-check.
The enforcement built this cohort is what demanded this retro.

## Finding (through-line)
B16 diagnosed the failure ("capture is out-of-band → omission") and responded with
MORE PROSE RULES. This cohort tested whether prose fixes omission — it does not.
The durable fix is mechanical:

- etude-8hq.4 built a read-only audit (run + gate + pushed + cadence + docs-drift
  checks; strict per-bead mode; batch window mode; explicit allowlist).
- etude-8hq.1 put it on the critical path two ways: a `dogfood-close.sh` wrapper
  (ergonomics — one command captures run + gates and runs the terminal `--bead`
  audit) AND a `.beads/hooks/pre-push` hook that EXEMPTS `refs/etude/*` pushes
  (so capture pushes pass) and BLOCKS `refs/heads/*` code pushes when the batch
  `--last 9` audit fails.

Proof it works: this retro was triggered by the audit's own WARN, and the 8hq.1
code push was gated live by the hook (audit ran, passed, push allowed).

## What went wrong / was caught
1. **`grep -c … || echo 0` bug (8hq.4):** `grep -c` prints `0` AND exits non-zero
   on no-match, so `|| echo 0` appended a SECOND line, breaking the arithmetic and
   silently disabling the docs-drift check. Caught at verify. Recurring shell
   footgun — use `|| true`, not `|| echo 0`.
2. **8hq.1 plan rejected the stronger design on a false premise:** the plan
   rejected a pre-push hook ("can't see the bead id", "would recurse"). One
   adversarial seat re-derived the premise from source — the hook needs no bead id
   (batch audit) and doesn't recurse (etude-only pushes are exempt) — and BLOCKed,
   overriding a 2-GO majority. Durable fix: runbook Plan-Phase Discipline **P3**
   (rejected-alternatives rationale is a prime BLOCK target; gate resolution is not
   a vote count).

## What worked well (preserve)
The multi-seat panel earned its keep: a lone constructive BLOCK that NAMED a
feasible better mechanism produced a materially better design than the comfortable
majority. Keep running adversarial seats against the plan's REASONING, not just its
diff.

## Durable changes landed
- 8hq.4 audit + 8hq.1 close wrapper + `.beads/hooks/pre-push` hook (commit 7d8771f).
- Runbook Plan-Phase Discipline P3 + the not-a-vote-count corollary.
- Ledger entry B17 (dual-output with this artifact).

## Decision
informational — process retro; the durable changes are already implemented.
